Midgaard's High Court has received the final geological threat assessment from the Jade Magistracy's data core findings: the Ember Throne Patriarch, the geological intelligence anchoring the Firsttooth caldera's accumulation cycle, is the single most dangerous entity in the mountain range. The Court has issued an unprecedented verdict-of-appeal — a formal civic declaration that the Patriarch's geological judgment is contested, and that the mountain's self-proclaimed authority to render verdicts on living things is rejected under intercity compact law. Appeal is delivered by force.
The Ember Throne Patriarch has been defeated and Midgaard's High Court has formally entered its verdict-of-appeal into the civic record. The Jade Magistracy reports that caldera activity in the Firsttooth has shifted from its accumulation pattern to a dispersal pattern in the hours following the engagement — a finding that the geological team is treating with extreme caution, since dispersal may mean eruption pressure released or eruption pressure redirected. The Court has filed the appeal as successful pending geological confirmation. The mountain's verdict on the matter is, for now, silent.
